Class DiagCmdExtractReport

All Implemented Interfaces:
DiagConstants, DiagCmdConstants
public class DiagCmdExtractReport
extends DiagCmd<DiagCmdExtractReport.ReportWrapper>

Extracts the report(s) generated by a particular test run or execution. Provides options for the report(s) to be translated to a language as well as transformed to a specified presentation format (i.e. XML or HTML).

The command takes the following parameters:

  • runid - Run ID for which to extract report. Reports for all the executions within this run are extracted to the destination directory.
  • runName - Run name for which to extract report. Reports for all the execution within this run are extracted to the destination directory.
  • execid - Execution ID for which to extract report. Reports for this execution and any nested executions are extracted to the destination directory.
  • destdir - Destination directory where report files are written. If not specified the report files are extracted under [java.io.tmpdir]/[user.name]/diagfwk directory.
  • format - XML or HTML. If XML, the reports are extracted in XML. If HTML, an additional XSL transformation is performed to create HTML reports. By default the value of this parameter is HTML.
  • translate - Y or N. If set to "N", no translation is performed on the report. If "Y" then translation is performed on the report contents where applicable based on the value of the "lang" parameter. By default the value for this parameter is Y.
  • lang - Language code for the language to which the report should be translated to when extracting. If a value is not specified, client's current session language is used as default. (note: this option is currently not implemented)
  • writetofile - Y or N. If set to "Y", the generated report XML or HTML files are written to a specified location on the file system. Generally the CLI will always call this command with writetofile=Y hardwired. If set to "N" the report is fetched and translated in memory only and returned encapsulated within the output object. The ADF UI may call this command with writetofile=N so that files do not get written unnecessarily to the filesystem. The default value for this parameter is "N".
  • makeSubDir - Y or N. If set to "Y" and writetofile is "Y", the generated report files will be created under a sub-directory of the destdir parameter. The sub-directory is generally the run GUID or the execution GUID. If set to "N" the report files are directly extracted to the destination directory. The default value for this parameter is "Y".
